OL,5,G2200 Father Ted
OL,6,     FChirpy Burpy Cheap Sheep: Ted is
OL,7,     Fso confident of Chris the Sheep's
OL,8,     Fperformance at the annual sheep
OL,9,     Ftrials that he bets the entire
OL,10,     Fyearly heating allowance on the
OL,11,     Fbeast to win.
OL,12,G2235 Father Ted
OL,13,     FSpeed 3: Pat Mustard, Craggy
OL,14,     FIsland's milkman, is sacked, so
OL,15,     FDougal takes over the round. When
OL,16,     FPat plants a bomb on the float for
OL,17,     Frevenge, Ted must keep his nerve
OL,18,     Fto save Dougal.
